In his remarks at the United Nations, President Trump expressed his belief in the tremendous potential of the United Nations. He acknowledged that he had been a critic in the past but recognized the importance of the UN as a forum for solving world problems. Trump praised UN Secretary General and commended his leadership, as well as the work of Nikki Haley and Rex Tillerson. He toasted to the potential of both the United States and the United Nations, expressing his confidence in their ability to achieve great things.